title: Caught
tags: autumnleaves neighboursyard intheneighbourhood gabianwall rocks metal gold bokeh macrolens throughherlens
description_content:
A fallen leaf is nothing more than a summerâ€™s wave goodbye.
~ Unknown

Our neighbours put in a gabian wall around their yard. It is low enough to catch the autumn leaves falling. Walking by, I had to capture the leaves caught between the slats. The next day, the neighbours came along and removed them all and put them in compost. I think they're going to be busy :)
